<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Nemisis Dragon on 04-25-2002 03:29 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL"> [QUOTE]Originally posted by Ragon der Magier:
[i]Has s.o. watched the show entirely and can give a round-up on what was their judgement?
[/i][/QUOTE]

I watched it yesterday so here's a kind of report, which includes my opinion about the reporter, who presented it.

In the first take the reporter Jörg showed the technolgy test. He talked about the Direct X 6.0 support (message of the test) and that it's normal that all have Direc X 6.0 or higher. Then he explains why his great computer did only have about 65fps @ 1024x786. It has to done with his TFT monitor and the refresh rate. He was right  ;)

In the second take he showed the tester-room video. Jörg thought that all testers played the game in LAN (  :D) and that the background music of the video gave the watcher a kind of sad atmosphere like "You have to play this game now!". He also said that the video, even with this low-qualitiy, looks good and detailed. While showing it he talked from time to time about the actual status of the vote.
After he showed nearly the complete video he played the last special feature movie "What's in a scene?". There he was too silly to bring it on the full screen (with ALT+ENTER) and claims about this little window. He couldn't also explain what the videos shows and didn't know what the skills do in the first scene with Kistandalius’ shop. There it was clear for myself, that the reporter wasn't really appointed to his job. 
At last he said that it looks really similar to Baldur's Gate 2 (hehe no Diablo  ;) ) and that we have to wait and see if it will be a good RPG or not, like the vote says.

</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
